** 30-7-2022

The argument that immigration (documented or otherwise) depresses wages by introducing more competition in the labor market is very appealing. Today someone pointed out that it doesn't make sense because it doesn't show the whole picture. Sure, there will be an influx of people in the job market, but also literally every other market. So not only does the supply of workers go up, the demand does too, since the immigrants need doctors, restaurants, and so on, too.
